# app-earn environment — copy to `.env` and adjust for local dev.
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the client (via import.meta.env).
# There are NO secrets here; values are public URLs / addresses.

# Network ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Selects the on-chain address profile (see src/lib/chain/config.ts).
#   devnet  (default) — the live devnet earn/staking deployment.
#   mainnet           — the mainnet earn/staking deployment.
# Unset / unknown → devnet (fail-safe default; existing builds unchanged).
VITE_NETWORK=devnet

# RPC transport (resilient: PRIMARY first, then automatic fallback to public RPC)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The shared Connection uses a custom fetch (src/lib/chain/rpc.ts) that tries a
# PRIMARY endpoint and, only on a transport-level failure (network error /
# timeout, or 5xx/429 on idempotent reads), transparently falls back to the
# public cluster RPC. It never falls back on a valid JSON-RPC error response and
# never double-sends a sendTransaction. PRIMARY precedence:
#   1. VITE_RPC_URL          — explicit operator override (private endpoint).
#   2. VITE_FAUCET_API_BASE  — backend JSON-RPC proxy at ${base}/rpc (below).
#   3. (neither)             — public cluster RPC, no separate fallback.
#
# Optional RPC override. When set, this URL is the PRIMARY (fallback stays the
# public RPC). Use a private endpoint (Helius / QuickNode) here, OR leave it
# unset and rely on the backend proxy (VITE_FAUCET_API_BASE) so no private RPC
# key is embedded in the web app / Seeker APK.
# VITE_RPC_URL=

# Meteora RWT/USDC DLMM pool (LB pair) address.
#   devnet  — defaults to the live devnet pool; override only if it is redeployed.
#   mainnet — REQUIRED at launch (C1). The pool does NOT exist on mainnet until
#             it is created at launch; set this to the new LB-pair address then.
#             While unset on mainnet the swap surface degrades gracefully
#             (market price shows "—", sell is unavailable).
# VITE_METEORA_POOL=

# Base URL of the backend API. Serves TWO things off one base:
#   - the JSON-RPC proxy at ${base}/rpc — becomes the PRIMARY RPC endpoint when
#     VITE_RPC_URL is unset (keeps the private Helius key server-side, so neither
#     the web app nor the Seeker APK embeds it). On failure the transport falls
#     back to the public cluster RPC automatically.
#   - the devnet "Get test USDC" faucet ("/faucet/earn-usdc"). The faucet
#     endpoint is devnet/localnet-only on the backend; on mainnet the affordance
#     is hidden regardless of this value.
#
#   Production : https://api.areal.finance
#   Local dev  : http://localhost:3010   (NestJS dev port)
#
# Leave unset/empty to disable the proxy primary (falls through to public RPC)
# and hide the faucet affordance entirely.
VITE_FAUCET_API_BASE=https://api.areal.finance
